<subSubSection id="FDD6BA782B9C583B0AF3C7EC2ECB876B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="0B70D47BD8C5CF1B15DF61450C73B0CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7B17C7898F13E31DB48B0A65291F061" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A very distinctive species because of the suburceolate, tubular corolla with exserted stamens combined with the white-tomentose stem and leaf indumentum. Leaves are mostly absent at anthesis.</paragraph>
